## First Supported Data Modes

The app should have three data modes during development:

### 1. Fixture Mode

Uses fake/test runs bundled in the repo.

Purpose:
- test engine
- test UI
- allow development before real files are available

### 2. Manual Test Import Mode

Allows selecting a local sample JSON/CSV file.

Purpose:
- test parsers
- test import pipeline

### 3. Real Local Import Mode

Reads Aimlabs/KovaaK's local/export data.

Purpose:
- real user value

Real local import becomes production only after we inspect real sample files.

---

## First Useful App Experience

The first useful version should let a user do this:

```text
Open Aim Brain
↓
Choose data source
↓
Import sample or real score file
↓
See imported runs
↓
Review unmatched scenarios
↓
See basic profile summary
↓
See one clear recommendation
```

If the app can do that reliably, the foundation is alive.

---

## Definition of MVP Done

MVP is done when:

- app launches
- local SQLite database initializes
- migrations apply
- sample runs import safely
- duplicate imports are blocked
- uncertain imports go to review queue
- scenario matching works with aliases/overrides
- benchmark definition validator works
- missing thresholds use progress-only mode
- same engine analyzes at least two sample benchmark definitions
- Home shows coach-first summary
- tests cover the core pipeline
